#summary List of possible objects
#labels Phase-Implementation

= Introduction =

A `possibles` is a list of NulFuzzyObj. It is used to represent computed objects.

== !JavaScript representation ==

A `possibles` is an a array of JsNulFuzzyObj.

The `possibles` array define beside these methods :
|| and || function(JsKlg, ...) || Creates a list of `possibles` who are these unifiable to the given ones ||
|| or || function(JsKlg, ...) || Creates a list of `possibles` who are these or the given ones ||
|| maybe || function(JsKlg, ...) || Modifies this `possibles` so that they recognise also the given ones ||
|| set || function() || Get these possibles as a NulObjSet representation (only valid if items are JsNulFuzzyObj) ||
